benak.tomas.crimemonitor.client

Class RetainedAsyncTask<Result>

  • java.lang.Object
      • benak.tomas.crimemonitor.client.RetainedAsyncTask<Result>
  • Type Parameters:
    Result - the async task result type
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    GetCrimeDataTask, GetKodAktualnihoUtvaruAsyncTask

    public abstract class RetainedAsyncTask<Result>
extends
    Author:
    Tom RetainedAsyncTask is the abstract base class for all wrapped async tasks.

    This async task asks for the configured URL, retrieves the resulting content and deserializes it to Result.

    This class can be attached to and detached from the AsyncTaskHandler, to which it reports its lifecycle events.

    See Also:
    AsyncTaskHandler

      • RetainedAsyncTask

        public RetainedAsyncTask()
        The parameterless constructor.

        Constructs a new RetainedAsyncTask. It does not provide the async task handler for this async task. The async task handler for this async task can be set later on by setAsyncTaskHandler(benak.tomas.crimemonitor.client.AsyncTaskHandler<Result>).
